  "issue_number": 555,
  "issue_title": "Tune ranked registry search for high-intent Claude workflow queries",
  "issue_body": "Parent epic: #550\nRefs: #487, #549\n\n## Goal\nImprove registry search so high-intent Claude workflow queries return the most useful entries first.\n\n## Requirements\n- Tune scoring for title, tag, keyword, category, source-backed, safety/privacy, and trusted-package signals.\n- Add fixture queries including `code review`, `browser automation`, `safe mcp`, `design skill`, `statusline`, and `raycast`.\n- Preserve bounded result size, current filters, and safe response shape.\n- Keep ranking explainable through `searchScore` and `searchReasons`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Exact and high-intent matches rank above broad substring matches.\n- Search filters still work with ranked ordering.\n- API responses remain bounded and public-safe.\n\n## Validation expected\n- `pnpm exec vitest run tests/registry-search-api.test.ts tests/registry-search-facets.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test`\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-15T08:18:48.000Z",
